<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='922496' id='t-922496'>It starts to search for its house in the right distance</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='925416' id='t-925416'>away from the food, but it is clearly completely lost.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='931391' id='t-931391'>So we know now that this animal uses path integration</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='935609' id='t-935609'>to find its way around, and the callous experimenter</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='939688' id='t-939688'>leads it top left and leaves it. (Laughter)</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
15:53
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='942809' id='t-942809'>So what we're looking at here are a group of animals</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='946864' id='t-946864'>that use a compass, and they use the sun as a compass</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='948943' id='t-948943'>to find their way around,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='950583' id='t-950583'>and they have some sort of system</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='953108' id='t-953108'>for measuring that distance,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='955071' id='t-955071'>and we know that these species here actually</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='958408' id='t-958408'>count the steps. That's what they use as an odometer,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='961089' id='t-961089'>a step-counting system, to find their way back home.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='966226' id='t-966226'>We don't know yet what dung beetles use.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
16:20
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='969049' id='t-969049'>So what have we learned from these animals</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='971328' id='t-971328'>with a brain that's the size of a grain of rice?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='974329' id='t-974329'>Well, we know that they can roll balls in a straight line</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='978440' id='t-978440'>using celestial cues.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='980585' id='t-980585'>We know that the dance behavior is an orientation behavior</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='983713' id='t-983713'>and it's also a thermoregulation behavior,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='986127' id='t-986127'>and we also know that they use a path integration system</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='990325' id='t-990325'>for finding their way home.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='992414' id='t-992414'>So for a small animal dealing with a fairly revolting substance</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='996584' id='t-996584'>we can actually learn an awful lot from these things</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='999353' id='t-999353'>doing behaviors that you and I couldn't possibly do.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1002985' id='t-1002985'>Thank you. (Applause)</span>
</span>
</p>
